{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place onions in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Heat oil in a non-stick frying pan over a high heat. Fry beef, bacon and chopped onions for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, rinse mixing bowl.","Place garlic cloves in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add carrots, red wine, water, salt, black pepper, bouquet garni and contents of frying pan then cook <nobr>30 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add mushrooms and cook again <nobr>40 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","For a thicker sauce, add cornflour and mix <nobr>2 min\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Serve hot, with rice or potatoes."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g onions, quartered","1 Tbsp olive oil","300 g beef (blade, shank, chuck or brisket), diced (2-3 cm)","75 g streaky bacon, cured and smoked, cut in strips (1 cm)","2 garlic cloves","150 g carrots, sliced (2 cm)","200 g red wine, full-bodied","150 g water","½ tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","¼ tsp ground black pepper, or to taste","1 bouquet garni (bay leaf, thyme and parsley)","100 g button mushrooms, brushed and sliced","1 - 2 tsp cornflour              (optional)"]}],"id":"r112545","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-HEVIkf2-YTA\/XZQxAURC5bI\/AAAAAAAAcqo\/zii-tQf6Megv99AXMNNOf1sYXJr_UQwIACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_jKoYnHa4hDHdlIbD.png","title":"Beef Bourguignon","publishedAt":"2016-05-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"42.2 g","fat":"23.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11.7 g","calories":"1785 kJ \/ 427 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frigideira, non-stick pan, fogão","hintsAndTricks":["This is a great dish to prepare a day in advance as the flavours will develop and the stew will be even more delicious once reheated."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","2 portions"]}